1
00:00:27,527 --> 00:00:30,948
THE HUSBAND

2
00:00:35,202 --> 00:00:36,410
THIS SERIES IS FICTITIOUS

3
00:00:36,411 --> 00:00:39,039
CHILDREN WERE FILMED SAFELY
GEN AI WAS USED IN SELECT SCENES

4
00:00:39,623 --> 00:00:42,876
You have one hour
to get my one billion.

5
00:00:46,463 --> 00:00:47,755
CALLING
FATHER-IN-LAW

6
00:00:47,756 --> 00:00:49,925
The number you dialed is not available…

7
00:00:51,134 --> 00:00:52,218
HOSPITAL FRONT DESK

8
00:00:52,219 --> 00:00:54,428
Is Dr. Ko at the hospital right now?

9
00:00:54,429 --> 00:00:55,973
He's currently in surgery.

10
00:00:59,142 --> 00:01:00,893
CALLING
MODU BANK

11
00:01:09,111 --> 00:01:12,196
TRAIN PASSING

12
00:01:25,877 --> 00:01:27,379
INCOMING VIDEO CALL
UNKNOWN NUMBER

13
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:34,761
Hello?

14
00:01:35,596 --> 00:01:37,139
And my one billion won?

15
00:01:40,976 --> 00:01:42,227
Each contains 500 million.

16
00:01:43,687 --> 00:01:45,104
One billion in total.

17
00:01:45,105 --> 00:01:48,649
Come to 43-87, Sajiro-gil.

18
00:01:48,650 --> 00:01:50,484
Be here within 30 minutes.

19
00:01:50,485 --> 00:01:52,988
If I don't get my one billion won,
consider your wife dead.

20
00:02:19,056 --> 00:02:21,223
Hey, are you okay?

21
00:02:21,224 --> 00:02:22,351
Let me call an ambulance.

22
00:02:22,934 --> 00:02:24,101
Just hang in there.

23
00:02:24,102 --> 00:02:26,980
Hey, my…

24
00:02:28,398 --> 00:02:30,149
My one billion won…

25
00:02:30,150 --> 00:02:33,445
What? I can't hear you.
Can you speak up a little?

26
00:02:34,279 --> 00:02:36,113
I said,
did you bring my billion won?

27
00:02:43,705 --> 00:02:45,540
Sir, are you okay?

28
00:02:46,249 --> 00:02:48,000
EPISODE 2

29
00:02:48,001 --> 00:02:49,085
Hey, man.

30
00:02:49,086 --> 00:02:50,504
Can you hear me?

31
00:02:53,548 --> 00:02:54,632
Sir.

32
00:02:54,633 --> 00:02:56,635
Hey!

33
00:02:57,219 --> 00:02:58,261
Whoa.

34
00:02:58,845 --> 00:03:00,514
Whoa.

35
00:03:09,022 --> 00:03:11,065
Dude, I think he's crazy.

36
00:03:11,066 --> 00:03:12,900
Let's get it on video.

37
00:03:12,901 --> 00:03:14,652
This guy's a psycho.

38
00:03:14,653 --> 00:03:15,862
What the hell was that?

39
00:03:16,613 --> 00:03:18,489
What's wrong with that guy?

40
00:03:18,490 --> 00:03:19,825
Geez, that scared me.

41
00:03:27,165 --> 00:03:29,250
Guys, did you…

42
00:03:29,251 --> 00:03:30,919
Did you see a guy…

43
00:03:31,795 --> 00:03:34,547
on a motorcycle around here
with a black helmet on?

44
00:03:34,548 --> 00:03:35,631
- Huh?
- He's coming this way.

45
00:03:35,632 --> 00:03:37,425
We got to run! Come on!

46
00:03:37,426 --> 00:03:38,801
Guy on a motorcycle.

47
00:03:38,802 --> 00:03:39,803
- Run!
-  Huh?

48
00:03:40,387 --> 00:03:41,847
Did you see a guy on a motorcycle?

49
00:03:42,431 --> 00:03:44,266
H-He went that way!

50
00:04:16,882 --> 00:04:18,008
Where the hell did he go?

51
00:04:40,030 --> 00:04:41,490
What the hell was that for?

52
00:04:42,324 --> 00:04:43,492
I'm busy as it is.

53
00:04:44,075 --> 00:04:45,410
Almost killed me out here.

54
00:05:35,585 --> 00:05:36,586
Hello?

55
00:05:38,713 --> 00:05:39,797
Hel…

56
00:05:39,798 --> 00:05:41,674
Where are you right now, sir?

57
00:05:41,675 --> 00:05:42,967
Hello?

58
00:05:42,968 --> 00:05:45,761
I thought we had an agreement!
Where the hell are you?

59
00:05:45,762 --> 00:05:46,763
Mr. Kang?

60
00:05:47,848 --> 00:05:49,516
What did I just see in those bags?

61
00:05:50,517 --> 00:05:51,725
What?

62
00:05:51,726 --> 00:05:52,811
The money.

63
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:55,272
Are you kidding me?

64
00:05:59,818 --> 00:06:01,987
Here's your 80 million won, as requested.

65
00:06:02,821 --> 00:06:04,281
Look, I have a favor to ask.

66
00:06:19,671 --> 00:06:23,257
Mr. Kang,
is this some kind of joke?

67
00:06:23,258 --> 00:06:27,053
No, it's not what you think.
I wanted to give you the full amount,

68
00:06:27,929 --> 00:06:29,306
but it's just…

69
00:06:30,515 --> 00:06:34,101
I was running out of time,
and I got desperate.

70
00:06:34,102 --> 00:06:35,353
I'm so sorry.

71
00:06:37,564 --> 00:06:38,856
You're sorry?

72
00:06:38,857 --> 00:06:41,358
NEO SEON YEONGJIN MEDICAL FOUNDATION

73
00:06:41,359 --> 00:06:44,946
You're saying you're sorry
after deceiving me like this?

74
00:06:47,449 --> 00:06:50,994
Mr. Kang, why are you trying
to pull a fast one on me?

75
00:06:52,787 --> 00:06:54,748
Do you know how disappointed I am?

76
00:06:55,582 --> 00:06:58,084
I trusted you with all my heart,

77
00:06:59,294 --> 00:07:01,004
and you betray me like this?

78
00:07:04,257 --> 00:07:05,925
I'm going to your wife now.

79
00:07:07,052 --> 00:07:09,304
I'm so angry and upset right now…

80
00:07:12,057 --> 00:07:14,391
that I'm going to shred her to pieces.

81
00:07:14,392 --> 00:07:19,314
THE HUSBAND

82
00:07:23,902 --> 00:07:26,612
When the heart
rate drops to 40 bpm or lower,

83
00:07:26,613 --> 00:07:30,241
one may experience lightheadedness,
syncope, or loss of consciousness.

84
00:07:30,909 --> 00:07:32,910
However, ironically enough…

85
00:07:32,911 --> 00:07:35,205
…the heart fights to keep beating
until the very end.

86
00:07:51,638 --> 00:07:55,391
While chest pain is the most common
early symptom of a myocardial infarction,

87
00:07:55,392 --> 00:07:58,477
women and diabetics
may display atypical symptoms

88
00:07:58,478 --> 00:08:03,775
such as shortness of breath,
indigestion, or severe fatigue.

89
00:08:04,359 --> 00:08:07,528
Moreover, around 20 to 30%
of patients experience

90
00:08:07,529 --> 00:08:09,697
myocardial infarctions
without any early signs.

91
00:08:09,698 --> 00:08:11,574
So, for an accurate diagnosis, they must…

92
00:08:26,673 --> 00:08:28,049
You didn't have to do that.

93
00:08:37,726 --> 00:08:38,727
Oh.

94
00:08:40,979 --> 00:08:43,356
Hey, you got a minute?

95
00:08:44,482 --> 00:08:46,151
Thanks for the drink.

96
00:08:50,405 --> 00:08:51,740
You're all by yourself again.

97
00:08:53,074 --> 00:08:54,492
Why are you always alone?

98
00:08:57,454 --> 00:09:02,000
You study alone, eat alone,
drink coffee alone…

99
00:09:04,627 --> 00:09:07,088
- It's just comfortable.
- Mmm.

100
00:09:09,215 --> 00:09:10,717
Are you just used to being alone?

101
00:09:11,301 --> 00:09:13,344
Or do you have to be alone
to feel comfortable?

102
00:09:20,226 --> 00:09:22,187
I'll see you around, Taeju.

103
00:09:23,772 --> 00:09:24,773
Hold on.

104
00:09:28,568 --> 00:09:30,028
How do you know my name?

105
00:09:36,326 --> 00:09:37,952
KANG TAEJU

106
00:10:04,479 --> 00:10:06,189
Heart rate.

107
00:10:06,773 --> 00:10:11,193
When resting, the human heart beats
around 60 to 100 times per minute.

108
00:10:11,194 --> 00:10:13,278
This is called the resting heart rate.

109
00:10:13,279 --> 00:10:17,116
However, the heart rate may
exceed 100 bpm and remain elevated,

110
00:10:17,117 --> 00:10:20,453
even without any physical activity
or external stimulus.

111
00:10:21,329 --> 00:10:23,832
This is called tachycardia.

112
00:10:24,999 --> 00:10:27,668
On the other hand,
when the heart rate is 60 bpm or lower,

113
00:10:27,669 --> 00:10:29,419
it's called bradycardia.

114
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:32,756
Both can be signs
of underlying conditions,

115
00:10:32,757 --> 00:10:36,343
including cardiac disorders,
such as arrhythmia or thyroid dysfunction,

116
00:10:36,344 --> 00:10:38,221
so one must be wary of both symptoms.

117
00:10:40,473 --> 00:10:46,019
That said, what is the most common
physical symptom a patient notices

118
00:10:46,020 --> 00:10:49,899
when their heart beats at an abnormal rate
due to tachycardia or bradycardia?

119
00:11:05,540 --> 00:11:06,541
Well…

120
00:11:08,168 --> 00:11:10,086
their heart races.

121
00:11:19,971 --> 00:11:21,806
I'm sharing your umbrella.

122
00:11:23,516 --> 00:11:24,517
How have you been?

123
00:11:26,060 --> 00:11:27,437
What's been going on with you?

124
00:11:28,396 --> 00:11:29,480
What do you mean?

125
00:11:31,858 --> 00:11:34,402
Where have you been for the past few days?

126
00:11:37,363 --> 00:11:38,489
Why do you ask?

127
00:11:39,282 --> 00:11:40,408
I mean, you know.

128
00:11:41,993 --> 00:11:44,370
I was used to seeing you around every day.

129
00:11:45,079 --> 00:11:46,581
So it got me wondering.

130
00:11:50,126 --> 00:11:51,461
Oh.

131
00:11:52,587 --> 00:11:55,005
I was stuck at home with the flu for days.

132
00:11:55,006 --> 00:11:57,050
I actually thought I was going to die.

133
00:11:59,802 --> 00:12:00,803
Flu?

134
00:12:01,387 --> 00:12:02,388
So that's what it was.

135
00:12:03,556 --> 00:12:05,767
- Are you better now?
- Yeah, much better.

136
00:12:07,435 --> 00:12:08,728
Were you worried about me?

137
00:12:13,733 --> 00:12:15,860
I was pretty worried about you.

138
00:12:17,445 --> 00:12:18,446
What?

139
00:12:19,197 --> 00:12:20,782
As I was lying in bed,

140
00:12:21,574 --> 00:12:25,328
all I could think about was,
"I bet he's feeling lonely."

141
00:12:29,916 --> 00:12:32,460
Why would you think that?

142
00:12:33,127 --> 00:12:37,047
Well, I assumed you'd be studying alone,

143
00:12:37,048 --> 00:12:40,510
eating alone,
drinking coffee alone, as always.

144
00:12:41,719 --> 00:12:43,304
But I wasn't around.

145
00:12:45,223 --> 00:12:47,183
I thought that'd make you more lonely.

146
00:12:53,731 --> 00:12:56,025
From the looks of it, I guess I was right.

147
00:13:00,029 --> 00:13:01,030
Thank you.

148
00:13:02,448 --> 00:13:03,449
For what?

149
00:13:06,244 --> 00:13:10,498
You know, for looking out for me, I guess.

150
00:13:11,291 --> 00:13:12,709
I wouldn't call it that.

151
00:13:13,543 --> 00:13:15,877
I don't know. Mmm.

152
00:13:15,878 --> 00:13:17,505
I guess you keep getting to me.

153
00:13:19,090 --> 00:13:20,550
So weird, right?

154
00:13:22,218 --> 00:13:23,219
What do you mean?

155
00:13:25,138 --> 00:13:27,140
How we're on each other's minds.

156
00:13:28,850 --> 00:13:30,685
And we barely know each other.

157
00:13:32,395 --> 00:13:33,563
I think it's weird.

158
00:13:34,355 --> 00:13:36,649
I don't get why I think about you so much.

159
00:13:38,609 --> 00:13:42,780
About how you're always alone,
how you're always eating alone…

160
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:45,950
But mostly, I keep thinking

161
00:13:47,410 --> 00:13:50,163
how lonely you'd be when I'm not around.

162
00:13:53,624 --> 00:13:56,002
I don't want to think
about any of that anymore.

163
00:13:59,797 --> 00:14:01,132
Will you be my boyfriend?

164
00:14:29,911 --> 00:14:31,871
I'm going to your wife now.

165
00:14:33,164 --> 00:14:35,249
I'm so angry and upset right now

166
00:14:36,334 --> 00:14:38,711
that I'm going to shred her to pieces.

167
00:14:40,213 --> 00:14:42,548
W-Wait, sir. Just…

168
00:14:43,091 --> 00:14:44,382
INCOMING CALL
FATHER-IN-LAW

169
00:14:44,383 --> 00:14:48,096
H-Hey! Wait. Wait a minute, sir.

170
00:14:48,679 --> 00:14:51,890
Look, I wasn't able
to reach my father-in-law,

171
00:14:51,891 --> 00:14:54,184
but he's calling me back right now.

172
00:14:54,185 --> 00:14:58,396
I can actually get you the money you want.
I promise. I swear.

173
00:14:58,397 --> 00:14:59,524
Are you kidding?

174
00:15:00,525 --> 00:15:02,276
You want another chance?

175
00:15:04,195 --> 00:15:07,990
I mean, have you no shame at all?

176
00:15:08,491 --> 00:15:10,618
I've given you so many chances already.

177
00:15:11,327 --> 00:15:12,410
You want another one?

178
00:15:12,411 --> 00:15:14,914
Yes, please j-just once.

179
00:15:15,832 --> 00:15:18,209
Give me a chance
to make up for what I've done.

180
00:15:21,003 --> 00:15:22,379
Don't do this, boss.

181
00:15:22,380 --> 00:15:25,132
No, please, wait. Please, sir! Just once!

182
00:15:25,133 --> 00:15:27,884
Please, just give me
one last chance, okay?

183
00:15:27,885 --> 00:15:30,721
Geez, you're making this so hard.

184
00:15:44,569 --> 00:15:47,070
You know, once at my old job,

185
00:15:47,071 --> 00:15:50,158
I made a few mistakes that
I could've been fired over, but I wasn't.

186
00:15:51,409 --> 00:15:53,661
Later, I asked the boss
why he didn't fire me,

187
00:15:54,495 --> 00:15:55,872
and he said…

188
00:15:58,124 --> 00:15:59,125
"Look, man."

189
00:16:00,001 --> 00:16:03,838
"Everyone deserves at least three chances
to be the best version of themselves."

190
00:16:06,465 --> 00:16:09,468
And it's not like harming your wife
will make me feel any better.

191
00:16:10,970 --> 00:16:12,180
So, Mr. Kang?

192
00:16:13,264 --> 00:16:15,098
This really is your last chance.

193
00:16:15,099 --> 00:16:16,475
Right, sir.

194
00:16:17,560 --> 00:16:20,687
I appreciate it. Thank you.
Thank you so much.

195
00:16:20,688 --> 00:16:22,522
I'm giving you a chance,

196
00:16:22,523 --> 00:16:25,942
but there will be compensation
for you breaking my heart, right?

197
00:16:25,943 --> 00:16:28,446
Yes. Of course there will be.

198
00:16:29,363 --> 00:16:30,822
Two billion won.

199
00:16:30,823 --> 00:16:31,824
Pardon?

200
00:16:33,326 --> 00:16:34,409
Two billion.

201
00:16:34,410 --> 00:16:36,537
Geez, is the line bad or something?

202
00:16:37,580 --> 00:16:38,873
No.

203
00:16:39,999 --> 00:16:41,791
I heard you. Two billion won.

204
00:16:41,792 --> 00:16:43,127
I'll give you two hours,

205
00:16:44,003 --> 00:16:45,962
but if you go back on your word,

206
00:16:45,963 --> 00:16:50,760
try to call the cops,
or disappoint me with another dumb stunt…

207
00:16:52,136 --> 00:16:53,137
I assure you,

208
00:16:54,263 --> 00:16:56,349
you will pay for it dearly.

209
00:16:57,683 --> 00:17:00,143
This is your last chance. Don't blow it.

210
00:17:01,729 --> 00:17:03,564
Hello?

211
00:17:11,322 --> 00:17:12,615
Yes, Father.

212
00:17:13,282 --> 00:17:15,868
We need to talk. It's about Seyun.

213
00:17:48,442 --> 00:17:49,443
Huh?

214
00:18:48,878 --> 00:18:51,297
Are you okay, Mother?

215
00:18:53,507 --> 00:18:55,843
How dare he do this to my daughter!

216
00:18:57,887 --> 00:18:59,889
Despicable piece of shit.

217
00:19:02,308 --> 00:19:05,436
I swear to God, I'll rip him to pieces!

218
00:19:07,396 --> 00:19:09,231
This can't be happening.

219
00:19:11,067 --> 00:19:12,484
Kidnapping?

220
00:19:12,485 --> 00:19:13,611
Blackmail?

221
00:19:16,197 --> 00:19:19,408
How could this
be happening to my daughter?

222
00:19:20,493 --> 00:19:21,827
But why?

223
00:19:24,997 --> 00:19:27,124
Is this all he sent?

224
00:19:36,967 --> 00:19:38,302
You got nothing else?

225
00:19:59,657 --> 00:20:01,325
UNKNOWN NUMBER

226
00:20:03,869 --> 00:20:04,954
DELETE

227
00:20:10,960 --> 00:20:13,212
Two billion won in two hours…

228
00:20:16,382 --> 00:20:17,633
Did he demand anything else?

229
00:20:20,803 --> 00:20:24,098
He said he'd hurt Seyun
if we went to the police.

230
00:20:24,807 --> 00:20:26,976
We can't get them involved,
no matter what.

231
00:20:31,605 --> 00:20:33,398
How much time do we have left?

232
00:20:33,399 --> 00:20:36,359
Oh, uh, we've got around
an hour and 25 minutes.

233
00:20:37,445 --> 00:20:40,405
We have to hurry.
I'll make calls to banks.

234
00:20:40,406 --> 00:20:42,700
You take the car and pick up the money.

235
00:20:43,701 --> 00:20:46,494
He may come after the money again,
so you go with him.

236
00:20:46,495 --> 00:20:48,204
Oh, yes. Of course.

237
00:20:48,205 --> 00:20:50,124
Okay, we'll be back.

238
00:20:50,750 --> 00:20:52,834
- Wait, honey. Just a sec.
- Huh?

239
00:20:52,835 --> 00:20:55,546
Come here for a minute.

240
00:21:01,886 --> 00:21:04,053
I'll ask them to arrange that.

241
00:21:07,183 --> 00:21:08,392
Got it.

242
00:21:10,060 --> 00:21:14,315
- Yes, hello? Is this the bank manager?
- We'll take my car.

243
00:21:59,652 --> 00:22:01,987
Father, I have to tell you something.

244
00:22:03,405 --> 00:22:04,990
- The thing is--
- It's you.

245
00:22:05,825 --> 00:22:07,284
This is your fault, isn't it?

246
00:22:10,246 --> 00:22:11,329
What is?

247
00:22:11,330 --> 00:22:13,707
This has to be happening because of you.

248
00:22:14,834 --> 00:22:17,878
What are you… What do you mean by that?

249
00:22:18,629 --> 00:22:22,298
Seyun isn't the type
to go around making enemies.

250
00:22:22,299 --> 00:22:27,179
You were probably acting all arrogant
and crossed the wrong person. Am I right?

251
00:22:28,848 --> 00:22:30,640
You were like that in the past too.

252
00:22:30,641 --> 00:22:33,394
You don't care about anything else
when you think you're right.

253
00:22:34,645 --> 00:22:36,188
You can't have changed.

254
00:22:42,736 --> 00:22:44,530
Well, say something!

255
00:22:45,072 --> 00:22:47,700
I'm asking you
if that's why this is happening!

256
00:22:48,409 --> 00:22:49,492
Damn it!

257
00:22:49,493 --> 00:22:50,994
That piece of…

258
00:22:52,288 --> 00:22:53,706
Crazy bastard.

259
00:22:55,124 --> 00:22:56,417
Give me a break.

260
00:22:57,126 --> 00:22:58,627
Seriously…

261
00:23:19,815 --> 00:23:21,108
Come on…

262
00:24:04,568 --> 00:24:09,030
CHOI HYEONSU
NATIONAL POLICE AGENCY

263
00:24:19,416 --> 00:24:20,542
How are you?

264
00:24:21,168 --> 00:24:24,545
I'm Jang Dosik, Captain
of Major Crimes Unit 1 at Seongjin Police.

265
00:24:24,546 --> 00:24:26,965
I've got a few questions for you.

266
00:24:26,966 --> 00:24:29,134
We don't have much time,
so if you don't mind.

267
00:24:31,053 --> 00:24:32,929
So the kidnapper got in your car,

268
00:24:32,930 --> 00:24:36,432
pretending to be your designated driver,
at around 1:30 a.m.

269
00:24:36,433 --> 00:24:40,019
I feel like I made the call a second ago.
You got here so quickly.

270
00:24:40,020 --> 00:24:43,564
Well, I just happened to be
in the area, so I got here fast.

271
00:24:43,565 --> 00:24:48,153
I guess today's just my lucky day.

272
00:24:48,779 --> 00:24:50,738
Remember what the culprit
looked like?

273
00:24:50,739 --> 00:24:53,617
Any scars, tattoos, or anything
we could use to identify him?

274
00:24:54,994 --> 00:24:57,413
No, nothing really comes to mind.

275
00:24:59,873 --> 00:25:02,501
And you didn't recognize
his voice either?

276
00:25:03,627 --> 00:25:05,128
Hello?

277
00:25:05,129 --> 00:25:06,755
Mr. Kang Taeju?

278
00:25:07,423 --> 00:25:08,923
Yes, speaking. Who's this?

279
00:25:08,924 --> 00:25:10,883
I'm the driver
who drove you to your house.

280
00:25:10,884 --> 00:25:11,968
UNKNOWN NUMBER

281
00:25:11,969 --> 00:25:14,387
Well, early this morning, sir.

282
00:25:14,388 --> 00:25:16,473
I'd never heard his voice before.

283
00:25:17,558 --> 00:25:18,642
And his face…

284
00:25:20,644 --> 00:25:23,981
I don't really remember
what he looks like either.

285
00:25:26,358 --> 00:25:27,442
- Choi.
- Yes, sir?

286
00:25:27,443 --> 00:25:29,777
Secure the security footage
around the area.

287
00:25:29,778 --> 00:25:30,779
I'm on it.

288
00:25:33,615 --> 00:25:35,367
The kidnapper could call
any minute now.

289
00:25:36,035 --> 00:25:38,661
We'll be tracking his location
in real time,

290
00:25:38,662 --> 00:25:41,497
so try to drag it out as much as possible.

291
00:25:41,498 --> 00:25:44,542
Culprits like him
like to feel like they're in charge,

292
00:25:44,543 --> 00:25:46,837
so try not to provoke him in any way.

293
00:25:47,880 --> 00:25:49,672
-  Okay.
- As for you two,

294
00:25:49,673 --> 00:25:51,632
never interfere or get worked up.

295
00:25:51,633 --> 00:25:54,469
If he catches on,
it'll put your daughter in danger.

296
00:25:57,222 --> 00:25:58,514
Understood.

297
00:25:58,515 --> 00:26:00,559
I appreciate your cooperation.

298
00:26:08,317 --> 00:26:10,194
Why did you call the police?

299
00:26:11,070 --> 00:26:13,739
I told you it would put Seyun in danger.

300
00:26:14,364 --> 00:26:15,908
I thought I'd made that clear.

301
00:26:16,492 --> 00:26:19,620
What, are we supposed to listen
to whatever this guy says?

302
00:26:20,370 --> 00:26:24,374
Of course he tells you not to call them.
He doesn't want to get caught.

303
00:26:25,584 --> 00:26:28,169
You don't understand.
This guy is extremely dangerous.

304
00:26:28,170 --> 00:26:30,422
That's why we called the police.

305
00:26:31,006 --> 00:26:32,925
You're not getting it. This guy…

306
00:26:34,468 --> 00:26:37,054
He's completely insane.

307
00:26:41,767 --> 00:26:44,727
He's a total psycho.

308
00:26:44,728 --> 00:26:47,563
All the more reason we need the police.

309
00:26:47,564 --> 00:26:49,649
We can't deal with him on our own.

310
00:26:49,650 --> 00:26:50,942
No, you don't get it!

311
00:26:52,152 --> 00:26:54,904
You're just putting Seyun
in more danger right now!

312
00:26:54,905 --> 00:26:57,825
You will not speak to my wife that way!

313
00:26:59,660 --> 00:27:01,286
She's my own daughter.

314
00:27:01,870 --> 00:27:02,871
You got that?

315
00:27:03,747 --> 00:27:06,625
I'm the one
who's the most desperate to get her back!

316
00:27:10,504 --> 00:27:11,505
Listen, Taeju.

317
00:27:12,297 --> 00:27:15,049
You've been in the palm of his hand,

318
00:27:15,050 --> 00:27:16,885
so you aren't thinking straight.

319
00:27:17,511 --> 00:27:20,180
This is where you have to
let us handle things.

320
00:27:20,764 --> 00:27:22,306
And don't get in the way!

321
00:27:22,307 --> 00:27:25,310
You have no idea what this guy's like.

322
00:27:27,771 --> 00:27:30,315
You just don't know
because you haven't dealt with him.

323
00:27:30,983 --> 00:27:33,151
Sir? I know this is tough,

324
00:27:33,735 --> 00:27:35,737
but you need to stay calm.

325
00:27:36,363 --> 00:27:37,364
Okay?

326
00:27:38,490 --> 00:27:39,491
Yeah.

327
00:28:19,990 --> 00:28:21,073
Anyone there?

328
00:28:21,074 --> 00:28:23,868
Please let me out of here!

329
00:28:23,869 --> 00:28:25,829
Let me out of here!

330
00:28:29,082 --> 00:28:30,208
Hey!

331
00:28:42,804 --> 00:28:44,264
Are you okay?

332
00:28:48,352 --> 00:28:49,937
Are you hurt at all?

333
00:28:52,064 --> 00:28:53,482
Who's there?

334
00:28:54,608 --> 00:28:56,485
I bet you're pretty confused.

335
00:28:59,321 --> 00:29:00,447
Who the hell are you?

336
00:29:01,239 --> 00:29:02,240
What do you want?

337
00:29:02,908 --> 00:29:06,536
Don't make loud noises.
You'll be in trouble.

338
00:29:10,374 --> 00:29:13,210
What the hell are you saying?

339
00:29:14,127 --> 00:29:17,923
Be quiet! You'll get us both in trouble.

340
00:29:20,968 --> 00:29:22,094
Huh?

341
00:29:38,485 --> 00:29:39,695
Hey.

342
00:29:41,989 --> 00:29:43,991
Excuse me, what did you just say?

343
00:29:45,033 --> 00:29:48,412
We'll get in trouble
with the guy who locked us up here.

344
00:29:51,790 --> 00:29:54,041
Are you locked up against your will too?

345
00:29:59,756 --> 00:30:04,051
Hey, how long
have you been locked up in here?

346
00:30:04,052 --> 00:30:05,553
There's no time.

347
00:30:05,554 --> 00:30:07,556
I'm running out of time.

348
00:30:09,057 --> 00:30:10,726
What does that mean?

349
00:30:11,977 --> 00:30:16,314
When the girl in the red hood
gets swallowed by the snow…

350
00:30:17,065 --> 00:30:20,443
By the pale white snow…
It's all over for me.

351
00:30:20,444 --> 00:30:21,486
It's over.

352
00:30:23,739 --> 00:30:25,073
Hey.

353
00:30:26,116 --> 00:30:30,537
Once she's completely
swallowed, I'll be done for.

354
00:30:56,730 --> 00:31:00,025
He might video call you again,
so you'll sit here alone.

355
00:31:00,650 --> 00:31:02,110
- Hey, Park.
- Yes, sir.

356
00:31:03,904 --> 00:31:08,157
We'll be monitoring in real-time,
so just try to focus on the call.

357
00:31:08,158 --> 00:31:10,368
And try to drag it out
as long as possible.

358
00:31:11,119 --> 00:31:13,705
I know you're nervous,
but your wife's life is on the line.

359
00:31:14,289 --> 00:31:16,041
You have to keep it together, all right?

360
00:31:17,125 --> 00:31:19,168
- Yeah.
- Two minutes left.

361
00:31:19,169 --> 00:31:21,629
- Oh, take them to their room.
-  On it.

362
00:31:21,630 --> 00:31:22,672
This way.

363
00:31:27,094 --> 00:31:29,221
Let's just focus on saving Seyun.

364
00:31:30,597 --> 00:31:32,682
Okay?

365
00:31:35,936 --> 00:31:36,978
Don't mess this up.

366
00:31:38,688 --> 00:31:39,689
Yes, sir.

367
00:32:24,109 --> 00:32:26,402
INCOMING VIDEO CALL
UNKNOWN NUMBER

368
00:32:32,033 --> 00:32:34,578
INCOMING VIDEO CALL
UNKNOWN NUMBER

369
00:32:37,622 --> 00:32:38,623
Hello?

370
00:32:41,293 --> 00:32:42,377
It's you, isn't it?

371
00:32:43,712 --> 00:32:45,379
Where are you, Mr. Kang?

372
00:32:45,380 --> 00:32:48,048
Oh, I'm at my in-laws' house right now.

373
00:32:48,049 --> 00:32:49,508
In-laws?

374
00:32:49,509 --> 00:32:50,759
Yeah, I mean,

375
00:32:50,760 --> 00:32:55,097
they managed to prepare the money.

376
00:32:55,098 --> 00:32:57,933
And I didn't want to take off
with so much money.

377
00:33:13,366 --> 00:33:14,575
You got him?

378
00:33:14,576 --> 00:33:15,910
LIVE TRACKING MAP

379
00:33:15,911 --> 00:33:17,037
He's in Mangok-dong.

380
00:33:18,079 --> 00:33:20,582
- Send the squad over to Mangok-dong.
-  Copy that.

381
00:33:24,461 --> 00:33:25,962
Huh?

382
00:33:26,463 --> 00:33:27,839
What's going on?

383
00:33:29,466 --> 00:33:32,134
Something's wrong.
It says he's in Useong-dong now.

384
00:33:32,135 --> 00:33:33,845
You said Mangok-dong.

385
00:33:35,055 --> 00:33:36,056
He's moving again.

386
00:33:37,015 --> 00:33:40,060
- He's in Jonghaeng-dong.
- What the hell are you talking about?

387
00:33:40,560 --> 00:33:43,062
He's bouncing the signal
with some kind of hacking tool.

388
00:33:43,063 --> 00:33:44,564
Well, do something about it!

389
00:33:53,531 --> 00:33:54,532
Hello?

390
00:33:55,992 --> 00:33:57,661
Anybody else at home?

391
00:33:58,954 --> 00:34:00,956
No, I'm here on my own.

392
00:34:02,332 --> 00:34:04,668
So you're the only one
on the line right now?

393
00:34:05,293 --> 00:34:06,378
Yes, that's right.

394
00:34:09,047 --> 00:34:10,882
So you're saying…

395
00:34:11,675 --> 00:34:14,844
I can say whatever I want,
since it's just you and me, right?

396
00:34:17,138 --> 00:34:18,139
Yeah, I'd say so.

397
00:34:18,848 --> 00:34:22,268
But first, don't you want to see the cash?

398
00:34:22,269 --> 00:34:23,352
Mr. Kang.

399
00:34:23,353 --> 00:34:25,105
Take a look. It's all here.

400
00:34:25,855 --> 00:34:29,024
No messing around this time.
I got it all in cash right…

401
00:34:29,025 --> 00:34:30,610
Mr. Kang Taeju!

402
00:34:36,950 --> 00:34:39,119
Yeah.

403
00:34:44,916 --> 00:34:46,668
Switch to the back camera for me.

404
00:34:48,461 --> 00:34:49,796
But why?

405
00:34:50,588 --> 00:34:52,882
Just switch it for me, all right?

406
00:35:00,098 --> 00:35:01,224
There you go.

407
00:35:06,229 --> 00:35:09,357
We're going to go through every nook
and cranny in the house.

408
00:35:10,233 --> 00:35:11,818
Do as I tell you.

409
00:35:17,741 --> 00:35:19,284
Okay, right there.

410
00:35:19,826 --> 00:35:21,995
Pan from left to right.

411
00:35:22,912 --> 00:35:23,955
Okay.

412
00:35:28,376 --> 00:35:30,170
What are you doing? Just do it.

413
00:35:34,716 --> 00:35:36,926
Okay, panning from left to right.

414
00:35:47,187 --> 00:35:48,563
And the other way.

415
00:35:56,488 --> 00:35:57,530
Stop.

416
00:35:59,074 --> 00:36:00,825
What was that noise?

417
00:36:02,118 --> 00:36:04,037
What? I didn't hear anything.

418
00:36:04,704 --> 00:36:06,539
Did you not hear that noise?

419
00:36:08,333 --> 00:36:09,584
No, I didn't.

420
00:36:13,713 --> 00:36:14,798
Oh, is that so?

421
00:36:17,967 --> 00:36:19,761
Turn it to your right.

422
00:36:20,387 --> 00:36:21,721
Okay.

423
00:36:22,430 --> 00:36:24,348
That's your left, boss.

424
00:36:24,349 --> 00:36:27,977
Your right is toward the kitchen,
where the noise came from.

425
00:36:33,066 --> 00:36:34,067
Oh dear…

426
00:36:43,952 --> 00:36:46,705
Keep pointing it that way
and walk toward it.

427
00:36:49,124 --> 00:36:50,208
Okay, got it.

428
00:37:15,316 --> 00:37:16,317
Stop.

429
00:37:25,243 --> 00:37:26,244
Mr. Kang.

430
00:37:28,163 --> 00:37:30,206
Now, turn to your right.

431
00:37:49,934 --> 00:37:51,561
I said, turn around.

432
00:38:05,700 --> 00:38:08,495
- Good Lord. I can't stand this anymore.
- Honey.

433
00:38:09,287 --> 00:38:12,748
Look, kid. Are you trying
to get my daughter back or not?

434
00:38:12,749 --> 00:38:14,374
Honey, don't do this.

435
00:38:14,375 --> 00:38:16,126
We said we'd let him handle it.

436
00:38:16,127 --> 00:38:17,253
Quiet!

437
00:38:18,296 --> 00:38:19,798
Give me that phone.

438
00:38:22,008 --> 00:38:24,426
This is Seyun's father.

439
00:38:24,427 --> 00:38:26,261
The girl you took away.

440
00:38:26,262 --> 00:38:29,139
I was going to hand
my son-in-law the money

441
00:38:29,140 --> 00:38:31,225
and stay quiet in the other room,

442
00:38:31,226 --> 00:38:34,394
but I can't trust him with this anymore.

443
00:38:34,395 --> 00:38:37,148
So from now on, you can talk to me.

444
00:38:38,316 --> 00:38:39,567
Put him back on.

445
00:38:40,151 --> 00:38:42,069
Trust me, young man.

446
00:38:42,070 --> 00:38:44,739
It'd be much easier if you talked to me.

447
00:38:45,782 --> 00:38:49,827
This deal is between Mr. Kang and me,
and he's the only one I'll speak to.

448
00:38:49,828 --> 00:38:52,287
Well, it's my daughter and my money!

449
00:38:52,288 --> 00:38:54,331
I'd listen if I were you.

450
00:38:54,332 --> 00:38:56,291
You can talk to me, all right?

451
00:38:56,292 --> 00:38:57,751
Hey, old man!

452
00:38:57,752 --> 00:38:59,461
What? "Old man"?

453
00:38:59,462 --> 00:39:01,213
I said put Mr. Kang back on.

454
00:39:01,214 --> 00:39:03,882
You little… Look here, punk!

455
00:39:03,883 --> 00:39:06,802
I get that you're a criminal,
but show some respect!

456
00:39:06,803 --> 00:39:08,595
How dare you!

457
00:39:08,596 --> 00:39:10,473
What the hell…

458
00:39:11,140 --> 00:39:12,933
Have you lost your mind, pops?

459
00:39:12,934 --> 00:39:15,352
What did you call me?

460
00:39:15,353 --> 00:39:18,021
You little… How dare you!

461
00:39:18,022 --> 00:39:22,068
Uh, sir? Why don't you talk to me?

462
00:39:22,777 --> 00:39:24,070
What do you want, lady?

463
00:39:25,321 --> 00:39:28,407
Fine, go on if you want
your precious daughter to die…

464
00:39:28,408 --> 00:39:31,201
Here's an extra billion won.

465
00:39:31,202 --> 00:39:33,579
If you let my daughter go,

466
00:39:33,580 --> 00:39:36,540
you can have this
on top of the original two billion.

467
00:39:36,541 --> 00:39:39,251
That's three billion won in total.

468
00:39:39,252 --> 00:39:43,255
Hold on, so if I bring you
your daughter right now,

469
00:39:43,256 --> 00:39:45,340
you'll give me three billion won?

470
00:39:45,341 --> 00:39:47,010
Yeah, that's right.

471
00:39:48,511 --> 00:39:51,431
But we want her back within an hour.

472
00:39:53,141 --> 00:39:54,225
After an hour,

473
00:39:54,976 --> 00:39:57,144
I'm taking off 100 million
every five minutes.

474
00:39:57,145 --> 00:39:58,187
No.

475
00:39:59,731 --> 00:40:01,357
So what you're saying is,

476
00:40:01,900 --> 00:40:04,192
if I just bring you your daughter
within the hour,

477
00:40:04,193 --> 00:40:08,113
that three billion won can all be mine?

478
00:40:08,114 --> 00:40:11,075
The final amount will
depend on what you decide to do.

479
00:40:11,659 --> 00:40:15,079
Uh… One hour, three billion?

480
00:40:18,708 --> 00:40:20,919
I'll be in touch within an hour.

481
00:40:21,544 --> 00:40:23,629
I hope you keep your promise, ma'am.

482
00:40:23,630 --> 00:40:25,548
It's currently 4:15 p.m.

483
00:40:26,257 --> 00:40:27,591
One hour, for three billion.

484
00:40:27,592 --> 00:40:28,843
Keep that in mind.

485
00:40:41,397 --> 00:40:42,565
Three billion?

486
00:40:57,163 --> 00:40:58,289
Hey.

487
00:41:02,001 --> 00:41:03,795
Can you not hear me?

488
00:43:19,472 --> 00:43:20,473
Are you all right?

489
00:43:21,974 --> 00:43:23,059
Careful there.

490
00:43:23,726 --> 00:43:25,144
You'll break your ankle.

491
00:43:26,437 --> 00:43:28,980
I wouldn't want my guest to get hurt.

492
00:43:31,943 --> 00:43:36,864
You know, I was really touched
by your mother's love for you.

493
00:43:38,533 --> 00:43:39,909
My mom?

494
00:43:42,620 --> 00:43:45,873
She's an incredibly generous lady.

495
00:43:47,917 --> 00:43:49,835
No, what am I even saying?

496
00:43:49,836 --> 00:43:51,295
You ready?

497
00:43:55,341 --> 00:43:58,719
Are you ready to say hi to your family?

498
00:44:04,642 --> 00:44:06,310
INCOMING VIDEO CALL
UNKNOWN NUMBER

499
00:44:07,770 --> 00:44:10,731
What? It's been nowhere near an hour.

500
00:44:12,441 --> 00:44:14,610
Ma'am, just do
what you did earlier. Be calm.

501
00:44:28,791 --> 00:44:29,876
UNKNOWN NUMBER

502
00:44:30,376 --> 00:44:31,459
Mom!

503
00:44:31,460 --> 00:44:32,545
Seyun!

504
00:44:33,504 --> 00:44:35,882
Oh, Seyun… Se…

505
00:44:36,507 --> 00:44:39,051
You okay, sweetie? Are you hurt?

506
00:44:40,136 --> 00:44:41,929
I'm okay.

507
00:44:42,597 --> 00:44:45,348
Oh, look at you, you poor thing.

508
00:44:45,349 --> 00:44:46,808
Seyun…

509
00:44:46,809 --> 00:44:48,894
- You got him yet?
-  I'll take care of it.

510
00:44:48,895 --> 00:44:50,937
Now it says he's in Gansu, China.

511
00:44:50,938 --> 00:44:52,522
Hang in there, okay?

512
00:44:52,523 --> 00:44:54,192
-  Se-Seyun…
-  Okay.

513
00:44:55,776 --> 00:44:57,152
Sir?

514
00:44:57,153 --> 00:45:00,572
Now you've seen
that your daughter's okay, right?

515
00:45:00,573 --> 00:45:05,494
Where do we go? Tell us,
and we'll be there with the money.

516
00:45:06,454 --> 00:45:07,496
No, it's fine.

517
00:45:08,581 --> 00:45:11,958
I'll take care of everything, ma'am.
Don't worry about a thing.

518
00:45:11,959 --> 00:45:13,544
Just stay comfortable at home.

519
00:45:17,173 --> 00:45:19,634
Sit on your comfortable couch

520
00:45:20,635 --> 00:45:23,345
and watch your precious daughter die!

521
00:45:23,346 --> 00:45:26,473
- Seyun!
-  Seyun!

522
00:45:26,474 --> 00:45:27,974
-  Wait!
-  No!

523
00:45:27,975 --> 00:45:31,853
- Sir! Please, sir!
- No…

524
00:45:31,854 --> 00:45:33,063
Why are you doing this?

525
00:45:33,064 --> 00:45:36,150
Just because you're rich,
you think you can mock me?

526
00:45:36,901 --> 00:45:39,278
No! Not at all!

527
00:45:41,739 --> 00:45:44,032
- No!
- That's not true!

528
00:45:44,033 --> 00:45:45,910
- Stop!
- It's not like that!

529
00:45:46,410 --> 00:45:47,494
No!

530
00:45:49,413 --> 00:45:52,207
- Please… I'm sorry!
- Seyun…

531
00:45:52,208 --> 00:45:55,043
You're sorry?
Well, sorry's not going to cut it.

532
00:45:55,044 --> 00:45:57,672
- Please! Please don't! Stop it!
-  Let her go!

533
00:45:59,507 --> 00:46:02,175
- No, you can't! Please don't do this!
- No, stop it!

534
00:46:02,176 --> 00:46:04,219
- Seyun!
- Honey!

535
00:46:10,851 --> 00:46:14,604
-  No! Seyun!
-  Seyun…

536
00:46:14,605 --> 00:46:17,065
Please…

537
00:46:17,066 --> 00:46:19,235
- Please… No.
- Seyun…

538
00:46:23,531 --> 00:46:24,991
No…

539
00:46:37,837 --> 00:46:39,171
Seyun.

540
00:46:44,593 --> 00:46:45,803
Seyun…

541
00:46:47,179 --> 00:46:49,806
- Se-Se-Seyun?
- Seyun…

542
00:46:49,807 --> 00:46:52,143
Open your eyes, Seyun.

543
00:46:57,732 --> 00:47:01,861
Se-Seyun, wake up, please.

544
00:47:04,572 --> 00:47:05,614
Honey…

545
00:47:10,828 --> 00:47:12,121
Honey…

546
00:47:12,872 --> 00:47:14,165
Honey…

547
00:47:18,252 --> 00:47:20,003
You bastard!

548
00:47:20,004 --> 00:47:22,131
I'm going to kill you!

549
00:47:22,631 --> 00:47:25,926
I'm… I'm going to…

550
00:47:26,635 --> 00:47:31,724
I'm going to find you
and tear you to pieces, you bastard!

551
00:47:39,774 --> 00:47:41,192
Huh?

552
00:47:42,151 --> 00:47:44,069
Se-Seyun?

553
00:47:44,070 --> 00:47:45,403
Se-Seyun!

554
00:47:48,532 --> 00:47:51,618
Look, she's still alive!

555
00:47:51,619 --> 00:47:53,453
Seyun!

556
00:47:53,454 --> 00:47:55,580
Seyun!

557
00:47:55,581 --> 00:47:57,165
- Seyun.
- Honey, she's still alive.

558
00:47:57,166 --> 00:47:59,835
- Can you… Can you hear me?
-  Seyun!

559
00:48:00,544 --> 00:48:01,712
Mr. Kang.

560
00:48:03,547 --> 00:48:05,298
Mr. Kang Taeju!

561
00:48:05,299 --> 00:48:07,050
Wait a second, I…

562
00:48:07,051 --> 00:48:09,886
- What do I do?
- I got it…

563
00:48:09,887 --> 00:48:11,262
Ah, ah, uh.

564
00:48:11,263 --> 00:48:14,474
Yes. sir. It's me again. Please go on.

565
00:48:14,475 --> 00:48:15,476
Listen.

566
00:48:16,268 --> 00:48:19,104
You just had to give me
the money you promised, simple as that.

567
00:48:19,105 --> 00:48:20,188
Right.

568
00:48:20,189 --> 00:48:22,732
Why do you keep making it so complicated?

569
00:48:22,733 --> 00:48:23,983
I made this clear.

570
00:48:23,984 --> 00:48:25,277
I said…

571
00:48:26,237 --> 00:48:28,571
I said I'd only talk to you,

572
00:48:28,572 --> 00:48:31,032
but you put those fossils
in charge of the situation.

573
00:48:31,033 --> 00:48:32,659
We're sorry.

574
00:48:32,660 --> 00:48:35,912
I-I'm sorry. I really am.

575
00:48:35,913 --> 00:48:38,791
I said I hate it
when people make things complicated.

576
00:48:39,375 --> 00:48:43,879
And I told you not to call the cops,
but you got not one,

577
00:48:44,422 --> 00:48:49,635
not two, but four pigs
in the house and lied about it.

578
00:48:50,428 --> 00:48:52,512
- He's watching us.
-  Why are you doing this to me?

579
00:48:52,513 --> 00:48:54,055
He might have an accomplice.

580
00:48:54,056 --> 00:48:55,598
- Go look outside.
- I'm on it.

581
00:48:55,599 --> 00:48:58,185
- I'm sorry, it's all my fault!
- Oh, God.

582
00:48:59,353 --> 00:49:02,272
Did you really think
you could fool me that easily?

583
00:49:02,273 --> 00:49:04,691
No, it's not like that.

584
00:49:04,692 --> 00:49:06,985
This is just a misunderstanding.

585
00:49:06,986 --> 00:49:09,529
My wife's parents called the cops
out of desperation

586
00:49:09,530 --> 00:49:12,699
because they had no idea
about the situation. I had no choice!

587
00:49:12,700 --> 00:49:15,952
- Yes. We're sorry.
- Excuses.

588
00:49:15,953 --> 00:49:19,123
Stupid excuses! I'm sick and tired of it!

589
00:49:20,082 --> 00:49:23,668
I just trusted you

590
00:49:23,669 --> 00:49:27,047
and did exactly what you asked me to do.

591
00:49:28,215 --> 00:49:30,801
So why are you doing this to me?

592
00:49:31,385 --> 00:49:34,013
I'm getting nothing but bullshit from you.

593
00:49:34,597 --> 00:49:36,723
You just couldn't
bring yourself to pay me?

594
00:49:36,724 --> 00:49:38,767
Is that why you're doing this?

595
00:49:40,144 --> 00:49:43,021
No. Not at all.
Absolutely nothing like that.

596
00:49:43,022 --> 00:49:44,064
Listen to me.

597
00:49:45,566 --> 00:49:48,193
You're going to pay
for disappointing me until the end.

598
00:49:48,194 --> 00:49:51,905
- No! You can't!
- No!

599
00:49:51,906 --> 00:49:53,781
- No!
- Seyun! No!

600
00:49:53,782 --> 00:49:56,410
You didn't keep up
your end of the deal, boss.

601
00:49:57,620 --> 00:49:59,163
And now, your wife's going to die.

602
00:50:00,831 --> 00:50:03,125
- No, please.
- Hey, Kang Taeju.

603
00:50:04,835 --> 00:50:06,128
This is on you.

604
00:50:07,087 --> 00:50:08,171
CALL ENDED

605
00:50:09,256 --> 00:50:10,840
- Sir! Please!
-  Seyun.

606
00:50:10,841 --> 00:50:13,092
Don't do this!

607
00:50:13,093 --> 00:50:15,596
Oh, Seyun!

608
00:50:16,096 --> 00:50:19,016
No, Seyun!

609
00:50:20,809 --> 00:50:23,646
This is my fault…

610
00:50:35,407 --> 00:50:37,368
Hey, play that last bit back.

611
00:50:37,952 --> 00:50:39,078
Yes, sir.

612
00:50:41,539 --> 00:50:43,749
…excuses!
I'm sick and tired of it!

613
00:50:44,375 --> 00:50:47,710
I just trusted you

614
00:50:47,711 --> 00:50:51,172
and did exactly what you asked me to do.

615
00:50:51,173 --> 00:50:52,423
"What you asked me to do"?

616
00:50:52,424 --> 00:50:54,760
I'm getting nothing but bullshit from you.

617
00:50:56,262 --> 00:50:58,389
Mr. Kang!

618
00:51:02,434 --> 00:51:06,396
You're under arrest for solicitation
of kidnapping and murder of Ko Seyun.

619
00:51:06,397 --> 00:51:09,315
You have the right to remain silent.
Your words can and will be

620
00:51:09,316 --> 00:51:11,735
used against you.
You have the right to an attorney.

621
00:51:13,821 --> 00:51:14,904
Come on.

622
00:51:14,905 --> 00:51:17,490
What… Why are you doing this?

623
00:51:17,491 --> 00:51:18,992
We'll talk down at the station.

624
00:51:18,993 --> 00:51:20,451
Wh-What on earth is going on?

625
00:51:20,452 --> 00:51:22,830
Wait a minute. Wait.

626
00:51:24,039 --> 00:51:25,374
What the hell are you doing?

627
00:51:26,625 --> 00:51:27,751
We just got a tip.

628
00:51:29,086 --> 00:51:30,212
What tip?

629
00:51:31,297 --> 00:51:33,841
So I said we should get divorced.

630
00:51:35,092 --> 00:51:36,593
But she said she didn't want to.

631
00:51:36,594 --> 00:51:38,929
Well, she said she'd never do it.

632
00:51:39,638 --> 00:51:40,889
Why's that?

633
00:51:41,724 --> 00:51:43,099
Because it's what I want.

634
00:51:43,100 --> 00:51:45,728
She doesn't want to
give me anything I want.

635
00:51:47,771 --> 00:51:49,355
I just trusted you…

636
00:51:49,356 --> 00:51:52,443
…and did exactly what you asked me to do.

637
00:51:53,402 --> 00:51:54,486
Yeah, talk.

638
00:51:55,779 --> 00:51:56,863
What?

639
00:51:56,864 --> 00:52:01,619
Good afternoon,
I have a tip about a renowned neurosurgeon

640
00:52:02,286 --> 00:52:06,165
soliciting the murder of his own wife.

641
00:52:07,625 --> 00:52:11,461
She doesn't want to
give me anything I want.

642
00:52:11,462 --> 00:52:14,547
Wait, isn't that your voice?

643
00:52:14,548 --> 00:52:16,924
I'm out of options now.

644
00:52:16,925 --> 00:52:20,012
Taeju, what am I hearing?

645
00:52:20,721 --> 00:52:22,598
Anyway, that being said…

646
00:52:25,309 --> 00:52:29,688
I want you to get rid of my wife.

647
00:52:30,356 --> 00:52:31,649
What did you say?

648
00:52:32,316 --> 00:52:34,360
Get rid of my wife.

649
00:52:35,861 --> 00:52:37,237
I'll pay you, okay?

650
00:52:38,656 --> 00:52:40,740
I'll pay you 300… No.

651
00:52:40,741 --> 00:52:43,577
I'll pay you 500 million won.

652
00:52:44,161 --> 00:52:45,371
So please.

653
00:52:47,915 --> 00:52:49,832
Father, it's not what it looks like.

654
00:52:49,833 --> 00:52:52,210
- I can explain everything. Believe me!
- Take him.

655
00:52:52,211 --> 00:52:53,628
- Come on.
- What's going on?

656
00:52:53,629 --> 00:52:55,004
Say something!

657
00:52:55,005 --> 00:52:57,173
- Father, I can explain everything!
- Get moving!

658
00:52:57,174 --> 00:53:00,386
You bastard!

659
00:53:02,262 --> 00:53:03,805
- Take him to the station.
- Got it.

660
00:53:59,945 --> 00:54:01,112
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

661
00:54:01,113 --> 00:54:02,740
TAKING ACCOUNTABILITY
FOR THE PEOPLE

662
00:54:06,618 --> 00:54:07,661
Mr. Kang.

663
00:54:09,663 --> 00:54:11,457
How do you know the kidnapper?

664
00:54:12,666 --> 00:54:14,084
I don't know him.

665
00:54:15,002 --> 00:54:17,587
He showed up when I called for a driver.

666
00:54:17,588 --> 00:54:19,465
So you solicited

667
00:54:20,591 --> 00:54:22,801
a complete stranger to murder your wife?

668
00:54:23,802 --> 00:54:25,679
I never solicited anything.

669
00:54:27,681 --> 00:54:32,185
I want you to get rid of my wife.

670
00:54:32,186 --> 00:54:33,896
What? What did you say?

671
00:54:34,480 --> 00:54:36,230
Get rid of my wife.

672
00:54:36,231 --> 00:54:38,233
I'll pay you, okay?

673
00:54:39,151 --> 00:54:41,652
- I'll pay you 300… No.
- So what did you mean by that?

674
00:54:41,653 --> 00:54:44,238
I'll pay you 500 million won.

675
00:54:44,239 --> 00:54:45,907
- So please.
- Well…

676
00:54:45,908 --> 00:54:50,621
I was drunk out of my mind at that time.

677
00:54:55,542 --> 00:55:00,756
Honestly, I don't really remember.
And I don't know why I said that.

678
00:55:02,591 --> 00:55:04,593
You know where Ms. Ko is, don't you?

679
00:55:05,302 --> 00:55:06,887
Is she with your accomplice?

680
00:55:08,013 --> 00:55:09,514
Mr. Kang Taeju.

681
00:55:09,515 --> 00:55:11,725
Mr. Kang, where's your accomplice?

682
00:55:14,186 --> 00:55:16,312
I really don't know.
I didn't put him up to it.

683
00:55:16,313 --> 00:55:18,272
Tell us. You know where she is!

684
00:55:18,273 --> 00:55:20,526
I said I don't know!

685
00:55:26,615 --> 00:55:29,492
The… Yes, the tip you got.

686
00:55:29,493 --> 00:55:31,452
I'm sure it's from him.

687
00:55:31,453 --> 00:55:34,288
You can just track the IP or something.

688
00:55:34,289 --> 00:55:38,085
IP says that email
came from Nanning, China.

689
00:55:40,921 --> 00:55:42,630
You didn't see this coming, did you?

690
00:55:42,631 --> 00:55:44,382
Your accomplice…

691
00:55:44,383 --> 00:55:47,552
He's way more dangerous than you think.

692
00:55:47,553 --> 00:55:49,721
You're going to end up
taking the fall alone.

693
00:55:53,976 --> 00:55:55,602
Like I told you, I have no idea.

694
00:55:58,939 --> 00:56:01,191
Don't do this, man.

695
00:56:01,942 --> 00:56:03,026
Just be honest.

696
00:56:03,652 --> 00:56:05,112
Where's Ms. Ko?

697
00:56:06,029 --> 00:56:07,030
I don't know.

698
00:56:08,156 --> 00:56:10,534
Just how many times do I have to tell you?

699
00:56:11,326 --> 00:56:13,287
You're losing time here!

700
00:56:14,246 --> 00:56:18,165
Do you have any idea
what a waste of time this is?

701
00:56:18,166 --> 00:56:21,836
This guy is a psycho!
My wife is in danger!

702
00:56:21,837 --> 00:56:23,004
Calm down, Mr. Kang.

703
00:56:23,005 --> 00:56:27,133
I'm serious!
There's no time to be screwing around!

704
00:56:27,134 --> 00:56:28,635
Mr. Kang!

705
00:56:35,726 --> 00:56:36,727
Calm now?

706
00:56:42,941 --> 00:56:45,569
Hey, say something.

707
00:56:47,070 --> 00:56:49,364
Don't leave me here all by myself.

708
00:57:02,878 --> 00:57:05,504
Wash your face off.
And freshen up a little.

709
00:57:05,505 --> 00:57:06,756
That one doesn't work.

710
00:57:06,757 --> 00:57:07,883
Use the next one.

711
00:57:14,014 --> 00:57:15,015
What the hell?

712
00:57:17,351 --> 00:57:20,770
Man, it's about time
they fix this place up.

713
00:57:20,771 --> 00:57:22,898
Nothing works in here.

714
00:57:27,653 --> 00:57:29,487
Oh, hey, Captain Kim.

715
00:57:29,488 --> 00:57:31,865
Yeah.  It's been too long.

716
00:57:32,532 --> 00:57:34,533
Oh, that? Yeah, it was really helpful.

717
00:57:34,534 --> 00:57:36,202
Take your time, okay?

718
00:57:36,203 --> 00:57:39,206
Right, I was going to come and see you.

719
00:57:51,635 --> 00:57:53,260
Damn it.

720
00:58:04,648 --> 00:58:06,816
- What the hell, man?
-  Hey, come over here!

721
00:58:06,817 --> 00:58:08,401
What's that? No, not you.

722
00:58:08,402 --> 00:58:10,487
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

723
00:58:13,031 --> 00:58:15,534
I don't have time to waste here.

724
00:58:17,035 --> 00:58:20,080
I didn't do it, but everyone thinks I did.

725
00:58:21,581 --> 00:58:23,500
No one believes me.

726
00:58:24,626 --> 00:58:25,919
Who would?

727
00:58:30,215 --> 00:58:31,633
No one believes you.

728
00:58:33,093 --> 00:58:35,345
Why would anyone believe you, Mr. Kang?

729
00:58:40,642 --> 00:58:41,852
Who are you?

730
00:58:47,149 --> 00:58:48,191
What do you want?

731
00:58:53,447 --> 00:58:55,031
I said, who are you?

732
00:58:55,574 --> 00:59:00,704
I'm the only one who knows
you didn't plot your wife's death.

733
00:59:02,789 --> 00:59:03,790
What?

734
00:59:13,258 --> 00:59:18,179
THE HUSBAND

735
00:59:58,220 --> 01:00:01,764
If you want to find your wife,
come to 543-7, Shinyu-dong.

736
01:00:01,765 --> 01:00:03,516
Remember. Get there by 11 p.m.

737
01:00:03,517 --> 01:00:04,642
Mr. Kang!

738
01:00:04,643 --> 01:00:05,769
Get him!

739
01:00:06,269 --> 01:00:09,855
Police took over 20 minutes
to arrive, allowing the suspect to escape.

740
01:00:09,856 --> 01:00:13,108
How's my brother the suspect
when his wife's been kidnapped?

741
01:00:13,109 --> 01:00:14,193
It wasn't you, was it?

742
01:00:14,194 --> 01:00:16,695
Seyun will be in more danger
if I stay at the station.

743
01:00:16,696 --> 01:00:17,822
Stay away!

744
01:00:17,823 --> 01:00:20,784
Visual on suspect vehicle.
Requesting backup.

745
01:00:22,577 --> 01:00:24,578
This is how much time
you have left.

746
01:00:24,579 --> 01:00:27,790
When the sand runs out, you're dead.

747
01:00:27,791 --> 01:00:29,709
I have to save Seyun.

748
01:00:30,210 --> 01:00:32,212
Translated by Hyun Sik Yoon
